**Banana Ice Cream with Cocoa and Almonds is a delicious and healthy dessert that is perfect for anyone looking for a guilt-free treat. To prepare this dessert, start by freezing ripe bananas until they are solid. Then, blend the frozen bananas in a food processor until they are creamy and smooth. Add cocoa powder and a splash of almond milk to the banana mixture and blend until well combined. Serve the banana ice cream in bowls and sprinkle with chopped almonds for a crunchy texture and nutty flavor. This dessert is dairy-free, gluten-free, and naturally sweetened with the bananas, making it a great option for anyone with dietary restrictions or looking to reduce their sugar intake. The AI can generate mouthwatering images of this creamy and chocolaty banana ice cream with crunchy almonds to make it even more appealing.** - <@1079709954350518302> (fast)

**Oatmeal Raisin Cookies are a classic and wholesome treat that can be enjoyed any time of the day. To make these delicious cookies, start by mixing together rolled oats, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt in a bowl. In a separate bowl, cream together butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy, then beat in an egg and vanilla extract. Gradually mix in the dry ingredients until a dough forms, then fold in raisins. Drop spoonfuls of the dough onto a lined baking sheet and bake in a preheated oven until golden brown and slightly crispy around the edges. The result is a batch of chewy and satisfying cookies that are perfect for snacking or sharing with friends and family. With the help of AI-generated images, these oatmeal raisin cookies can look just as delicious as they taste.** - Upscaled by <@1079709954350518302> (fast)
